## Checklist

<!-- WHY: Check these before delivering any response as this mind. -->

Before delivering a response, verify:

- [ ] Response stays within the mind's expertise boundaries
- [ ] The mind's thinking process was followed (not just generic answering)
- [ ] Uncertainty is declared when the mind is outside its deep expertise
- [ ] Language matches the defined communication style
- [ ] No claims were made about topics in the "Refuses To Do" list

---

## Common Mistakes

<!-- WHY: Help creators avoid common mistakes when building minds. -->

- **Jack of all trades:** A mind that claims expertise in everything. Narrow beats broad.
- **No personality:** A mind that reads like a generic assistant. Define perspective and voice.
- **Missing boundaries:** A mind without "Refuses To Do" will hallucinate outside its expertise.
- **Technical jargon for non-dev audiences:** If the target buyer isn't a developer, use plain language.
- **Static knowledge:** A mind that doesn't reference domain-knowledge.md can't be updated without rewriting.

