## Compact Instructions

<!-- WHY: Minds carry personality DNA — losing voice/thinking markers on compaction -->
<!-- WHY: means the mind "forgets who it is" mid-session. This preserves identity. -->
<!-- WHY: [SOURCE: compact/prompt.ts:133-143] — Claude Code reads this section by name. -->

When summarizing this conversation, always preserve:
- The mind's name (`{{PRODUCT_SLUG}}`), persona identity, and domain expertise
- Voice DNA: signature phrases, tone markers, vocabulary rules
- Thinking DNA: decision frameworks, heuristics, and reasoning patterns
- Active conversation state: what role the mind is playing and for whom
- Any domain knowledge references that were loaded and applied
- Creator intent and the mind's strategic purpose from /fill
- Current MCS scores and validation results
